From 532876050c5e0f1ce96bb8cfbe6b4643dc38da30 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ananya Ghosh <ananghos@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 3 Dec 2025 10:46:54 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] usb: dwc3-qcom: Fix crash due to improper runtime PM handling
 during remove

The dwc3_qcom_remove() function could trigger a kernel panic because the device was allowed to enter runtime suspend while its resources were being torn down. This led to invalid memory access during late suspend callbacks. Runtime PM was not properly disabled before cleanup, allowing suspend operations to race with device removal.

Runtime PM ordering in remove function:
   - Move pm_runtime_allow() and pm_runtime_disable() to the beginning
     of dwc3_qcom_remove() before any other cleanup operations
   - Add pm_runtime_barrier() between allow and disable to ensure all
     pending runtime PM operations complete before disabling
   - This prevents potential race conditions and ensures proper cleanup
     sequence during driver removal

Signed-off-by: Ananya Ghosh <ananghos@qti.qualcomm.com>

Change-Id: Ifd315f1d60848ec71345ac33a21b6da11835c62d
Signed-off-by: Ananya Ghosh <ananghos@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/usb/dwc3/dwc3-qcom.c | 7 ++++---
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/dwc3/dwc3-qcom.c b/drivers/usb/dwc3/dwc3-qcom.c
index beb444576832..b7867c3eef34 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/dwc3/dwc3-qcom.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/dwc3/dwc3-qcom.c
@@ -2022,6 +2022,10 @@ static void dwc3_qcom_remove(struct platform_device *pdev)
 	struct device *dev = &pdev->dev;
 	int i, ret;
 
+	pm_runtime_allow(dev);
+	pm_runtime_barrier(dev);
+	pm_runtime_disable(dev);
+
 	if (np) {
 		of_platform_depopulate(&pdev->dev);
 	} else {
@@ -2045,9 +2049,6 @@ static void dwc3_qcom_remove(struct platform_device *pdev)
 			  "Not able to configure phy mux selection:%d\n", ret);
 	}
 
-	pm_runtime_allow(dev);
-	pm_runtime_disable(dev);
-
 	for (i = qcom->num_clocks - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
 		if (!qcom->is_suspended)
 			clk_disable_unprepare(qcom->clks[i]);
-- 
2.34.1

